HEADWORD: Easeful
<hw>Ease"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Full of ease;
suitable for affording ease or rest; quiet; comfortable; restful.</def>
<au>Shak.</au> -- <wordforms><wf>Ease"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Ease"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

